(noun) used in apposition is the abbreviation of the 
<collectingCountry box="[1233,1301,1557,1583]" name="South Korea" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Korea</collectingCountry>
Institute of Ocean Science and Technology (KIOST).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="306" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,908,1979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1629,1655]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Remarks.</emphasis>
In 
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim, 2020" authorityName="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim" authorityYear="2020" box="[353,577,1629,1655]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Aphotopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kiost" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[353,577,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Aphotopontius kiost</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[584,647,1629,1655]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the inner coxal setae are present in legs 1–3, but absent in leg 4. This feature is shared by other four congeners only: 
<taxonomicName authority="Humes and Lutz, 1994" authorityName="Humes and Lutz" authorityYear="1994" box="[694,1121,1665,1691]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Aphotopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acanthinus">
<emphasis box="[694,711,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[726,849,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">acanthinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Humes, A. G. &amp; Lutz, R. A." box="[858,1121,1665,1691]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="337 - 345" refId="ref16592" refString="Humes, A. G. &amp; Lutz, R. A. (1994) Aphotopontius acanthinus, new species (Copepoda: Siphonostomatoida), from deep-sea hydrothermal vents on the East Pacific Rise. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 14, 337 - 345. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1548913" type="journal article" year="1994">Humes and Lutz, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Humes, 1996" authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1996" box="[1134,1432,1665,1691]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Aphotopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlanteus">
